                = \n| population_total                = \n| population_density_km2          = \n| population_density_sq_mi        = \n| population_metro                = \n| population_density_metro_km2    = \n| population_density_metro_sq_mi  = \n| population_urban                = \n| population_density_urban_km2    = \n| population_density_urban_sq_mi  = \n| population_blank1_title         = \n| population_blank1               = \n| population_density_blank1_km2   = \n| population_density_blank1_sq_mi = \n| timezone                        = \n| utc_offset                      = UTC +3\n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| coordinates                     = \n| elevation_footnotes             = <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = Postal code\n| postal_code                     = 5789\n| area_code                       = +964\n| blank_name                      = \n| blank_info                      = \n| blank1_name                     = \n| blank1_info                     = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n}}\n\n'''Al-Shu&#39;ala''' is a lower middle class district of [[Baghdad]], Iraq. It is heavily populated and its inhabitants are [[working class]] families of limited income. There is a [[Shia Islam|Shiite]] majority of nearly 99%, while the remaining population is [[Sunni]].\n\nAl-Shu&#39;ala features a canal that stretches from the far east of the city to the west called al Mashrou'(\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0634\u0631\u0648\u0639) or \"the project\". \n\nAl-Shu&#39;ala contains 27 sectors, including Al shu'ala (\u0627\u0644\u0634\u0639\u0644\u0629), Al rahmaniyya (\u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0627\u0646\u064a\u0629), Al dawanim (\u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u0627\u0646\u0645), Um najm (\u0623\u0645 \u0646\u062c\u0645), Al jawadain (\u0627\u0644\u062c\u0648\u0627\u062f\u064a\u0646), Al salamiyat (\u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u064a\u0627\u062a), Al sabiyat (\u0627\u0644\u0635\u0627\u0628\u064a\u0627\u062a), Al dahna (\u0627\u0644\u062f\u0647\u0646\u0629) and Al khateeb (\u0627\u0644\u062e\u0637\u064a\u0628).\n{{Administrative districts in Baghdad}}\n\n{{coord missing|Iraq}}\n\n[[Category:Neighborhoods in Baghdad|Shu'ala]]\n\n\n{{Baghdad-stub}}\n{{Iraq-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Noortaihi", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al-Shu%27ala"}
{"title_page": "1982 Intercontinental Cup", "text_new": "{{Infobox football match\n| title                   = 1982 Intercontinental Cup\n| image                   = ToyotaCup1982.jpg\n| event                   =\n| team1                   = [[Pe\u00f1arol]]\n| team1association        = {{flagicon|URU|size=30px}}\n| team1score              = 2\n| team2                   = [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]\n| team2association        = {{flagicon|ENG|size=30px}}\n| team2score              = 0\n| details                 = \n| date                    = 12 December 1982\n| stadium                 = [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]]\n| city                    = [[Tokyo]]\n| man_of_the_match1a      = [[Jair Gon\u00e7alves Prates|Jair]] ([[Pe\u00f1arol]])\n| man_of_the_match1atitle =\n| man_of_the_match1b      =\n| man_of_the_match1btitle =\n| referee                 = [[Luis Paulino Siles]] ([[Costa Rican Football Federation|Costa Rica]])\n| attendance              = 63,000\n| weather                 =\n| previous                = [[1981 Intercontinental Cup|1981]]\n| next                    = [[1983 Intercontinental Cup|1983]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1982 Intercontinental Cup''' was a [[Association football|football]] match played on 12 December 1982 between [[Pe\u00f1arol]], winners of the [[1982 Copa Libertadores|1982]] [[Copa Libertadores]], and [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], winners of the [[1981\u201382 European Cup|1981\u201382]] [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]. The match was played at the [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]] in [[Tokyo]]. It was Aston Villa's first appearance into the competition, whereas it was Pe\u00f1arol's fourth appearance after the victories in [[1961 Intercontinental Cup|1961]] and [[1966 Intercontinental Cup|1966]], and the defeat in [[1960 Intercontinental Cup|1960]].\n\n[[Jair Gon\u00e7alves Prates]] was named as [[man of the match]].<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toyotamvp.html \n |title=Toyota Cup - Most Valuable Player of the Match Award \n |accessdate=2009-05-12 \n}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 FIFA Council recognised all the trophy winners as club world champions with the same title to the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] winners, then as official<ref name=\":F152322\">\"Official (''plural'' officials), from the Latin '' offici\u0101lis.'' 1. The official word is also used to refer to what is recognized or derives from an authority. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.dictionary.com/browse/official|title=Official, definition|author=dictionary.com}} 2. Approved by the government or someone in power. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english-spanish/official|title=official|author=dictionary.cambridge.org}} It is synonymous with legal, legitimate, approved. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.thesaurus.com/browse/official|title=Synonyms for official|author=thesaurus.com}}</ref><ref name=\":F154232\">For FIFA statute, official competitions are those for representative teams organized by FIFA or any confederation. Representative teams are usually national teams but also club teams that represent a confederation in the interconfederal competitions or a member association in a continental competition cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|page=5|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/Regulations/uefaorg/Regulations/02/55/82/79/2558279_DOWNLOAD.pdf|title=2018/19 UEFA Champions League regulations|page=10}}</ref> \"[[Intercontinental Cup (football)#International participation|world champions]]\" FIFA.<ref name=\":F154233222\">\u201cWhile it does not promote the statistical unification of tournaments, that is, has not absorbed to the Intercontinental Cup (merged with FIFA Club World Cup in 2005), FIFA is the only organization with worldwide jurisdiction over continental confederations and, then, the only one that can confer a title on that level, ergo the title assigned by FIFA with Official Document to the winners of the Intercontinental Cup is legally a FIFA world title.\"  cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|last=|first=|date=|website=|page=19|format=PDF|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}} cfr.</ref><ref name=\"FIFA201732\">{{cite press release|date=27 October 2017|title=FIFA Council approves key organisational elements of the FIFA World Cup|url=https://www.fifa.com/about-fifa/news/y=2017/m=10/news=fifa-council-approves-key-organisational-elements-of-the-fifa-world-cu-2917722.html|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/fifa-acepta-propuesta-de-conembol-de-reconocer-titulos-de-copa-intercontinental-como-mundiales-de|title=FIFA acepta propuesta de CONMEBOL de reconocer t\u00edtulos de copa intercontinental como mundiales de clubes|date=29 October 2017|publisher=conmebol.com|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"kit201822\">{{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13|format=PDF}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Yamazaki-nabisco-Cup final 2004.jpg|thumb|left|300px|[[National Stadium (Tokyo)|Olympic Stadium]], [[Tokyo]], hosted the final]]\n{{-}}\n\n==Match details==\n{{footballbox\n|date       = 12 December 1982\n|time       =\n|team1      = [[Pe\u00f1arol]] {{flagicon|URU}}\n|score      = 2\u20130\n|report     = https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/61688/\n|team2      = {{flagicon|ENG}} [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]\n|goals1     = [[Jair Gon\u00e7alves Prates|Jair]] {{goal|27}} <br> [[Walkir Silva|Silva]] {{goal|68}}\n|goals2     =\n|stadium    = [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]], [[Tokyo]]\n|attendance = 63,000\n|referee    = [[Luis Paulino Siles]] ([[Costa Rican Football Federation|Costa&nbsp;Rica]]) }}\n\n{| width=92% |\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _pe\u00f1arol8083h\n| pattern_ra = _pe\u00f1arol8083h\n| pattern_b  = _pe\u00f1arol8083h\n| pattern_sh = _pe\u00f1arol8083h\n| pattern_so = _3_stripes_black\n| leftarm    = ffdf00\n| body       = ffdf00\n| rightarm   = ffdf00\n| shorts     = 000000\n| socks      = ffdf00\n| title      = Pe\u00f1arol\n}}\n|{{Football kit\n | pattern_la =\n | pattern_b  = _thinskycollar\n | pattern_ra =\n | pattern_sh = _black_stripes2\n | pattern_so = _2_black_stripes\n | leftarm    = 88A7E0\n | body       = 970045\n | rightarm   = 88A7E0\n | shorts     = FFFFFF\n | socks      = 88A7E0\n | title      = Aston Villa\n}}\n|}\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size: 90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|\n|-\n!width=\"25\"| !!width=\"25\"|\n|-\n| ||'''1''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Gustavo Fern\u00e1ndez (Uruguayan footballer)|Gustavo Fern\u00e1ndez]]\n|-\n| ||'''2''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Walter Olivera]]\n|-\n| ||'''3''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Nelson Guti\u00e9rrez]]\n|-\n| ||'''4''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[V\u00edctor Diogo]]\n|-\n| ||'''5''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Miguel Bossio]]\n|-\n| ||'''6''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Juan Vicente Morales]]\n|-\n| ||'''7''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Venancio Ramos]]\n|-\n| ||'''8''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Mario Saralegui]]\n|-\n| ||'''9''' ||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Fernando Morena]]\n|-\n| ||'''10'''||{{flagicon|BRA|1968}} [[Jair Gon\u00e7alves Prates]]\n|-\n| ||'''11'''||{{flagicon|URU}} [[Walkir Silva]]\n|-\n|colspan=4|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"|{{flagicon|URU}} [[Hugo Bagnulo]]\n|}\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size: 90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=center\n|colspan=\"3\"|\n|-\n!width=\"25\"| !!width=\"25\"|\n|-\n| ||'''1''' ||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Jimmy Rimmer]]\n|-\n| ||'''2''' ||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Mark Jones (footballer, born October 1961)|Mark Jones]]\n|-\n| ||'''3''' ||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Gary Williams (footballer, born 1960)|Gary Williams]]\n|-\n| ||'''4''' ||{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Allan Evans (footballer)|Allan Evans]]\n|-\n| ||'''5''' ||{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Ken McNaught]]\n|-\n| ||'''6''' ||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Dennis Mortimer]]\n|-\n| ||'''7''' ||{{flagicon|SCO}} [[Des Bremner]]\n|-\n| ||'''8''' ||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Gary Shaw]]\n|-\n| ||'''9''' ||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Peter Withe]]\n|-\n| ||'''10'''||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Gordon Cowans]]\n|-\n| ||'''11'''||{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tony Morley]]\n|-\n|colspan=4|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Tony Barton (footballer)|Tony Barton]]\n|}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[1982\u201383 Aston Villa F.C. season]]\n*[[:es:Anexo:Partidos internacionales del Club Atl\u00e9tico Pe\u00f1arol|Pe\u00f1arol in international football competitions]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Intercontinental Cup (football)}}\n{{Pe\u00f1arol matches}}\n{{Aston Villa F.C. matches}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n\n[[Category:1982\u201383 in European football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:1982 in South American football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:1982 in Japanese football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:Intercontinental Cup (football)]]\n[[Category:Aston Villa F.C. matches|Intercontinental Cup 1982]]\n[[Category:Pe\u00f1arol matches|Intercontinental Cup 1982]]\n[[Category:Intercontinental Cup (football) matches hosted by Japan]]\n[[Category:1982 in Uruguayan football|Inter]]\n[[Category:1982\u201383 in English football|Inter]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:December 1982 sports events in Asia]]\n[[Category:1982 in Tokyo]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football match\n| title                   = 1982 Intercontinental Cup\n| image                   = ToyotaCup1982.jpg\n| event                   =\n| team1                   = [[Pe\u00f1arol]]\n| team1association        = {{flagicon|URU|size=30px}}\n| team1score              = 2\n| team2                   = [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]]\n| team2association        = {{flagicon|ENG|size=30px}}\n| team2score              = 0\n| details                 = \n| date                    = 12 December 1982\n| stadium                 = [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]]\n| city                    = [[Tokyo]]\n| man_of_the_match1a      = [[Jair Gon\u00e7alves Prates|Jair]] ([[Pe\u00f1arol]])\n| man_of_the_match1atitle =\n| man_of_the_match1b      =\n| man_of_the_match1btitle =\n| referee                 = [[Luis Paulino Siles]] ([[Costa Rican Football Federation|Costa Rica]])\n| attendance              = 63,000\n| weather                 =\n| previous                = [[1981 Intercontinental Cup|1981]]\n| next                    = [[1983 Intercontinental Cup|1983]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1982 Intercontinental Cup''' was a [[Association football|football]] match played on 12 December 1982 between [[Pe\u00f1arol]], winners of the [[1982 Copa Libertadores|1982]] [[Copa Libertadores]], and [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], winners of the [[1981\u201382 European Cup|1981\u201382]] [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]]. The match was played at the [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]] in [[Tokyo]]. It was Aston Villa's first appearance into the competition, whereas it was Pe\u00f1arol's fourth appearance after the victories in [[1961 Intercontinental Cup|1961]] and [[1966 Intercontinental Cup|1966]], and the defeat in [[1960 Intercontinental Cup|1960]].\n\n[[Jair Gon\u00e7alves Prates]] was named as [[man of the match]].<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toyotamvp.html \n |title=Toyota Cup - Most Valuable Player of the Match Award \n |accessdate=2009-05-12 \n}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 FIFA Council recognised all the trophy winners as club world champions with the same title to the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] winners, then as official<ref name=\":F152322\">\"Official (''plural'' officials), from the Latin '' offici\u0101lis.'' 1. The official word is also used to refer to what is recognized or derives from an authority. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.dictionary.com/browse/official|title=Official, definition|author=dictionary.com}} 2. Approved by the government or someone in power. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english-spanish/official|title=official|author=dictionary.cambridge.org}} It is synonymous with legal, legitimate, approved. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.thesaurus.com/browse/official|title=Synonyms for official|author=thesaurus.com}}</ref><ref name=\":F154232\">For FIFA statute, official competitions are those for representative teams organized by FIFA or any confederation. Representative teams are usually national teams but also club teams that represent a confederation in the interconfederal competitions or a member association in a continental competition cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|page=5|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13|format=PDF}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/Regulations/uefaorg/Regulations/02/55/82/79/2558279_DOWNLOAD.pdf|title=2018/19 UEFA Champions League regulations|page=10}}</ref> \"[[Intercontinental Cup (football)#International participation|world champions]]\" FIFA.<ref name=\":F154233222\">\u201cWhile it does not promote the statistical unification of tournaments, that is, has not absorbed to the Intercontinental Cup (merged with FIFA Club World Cup in 2005), FIFA is the only organization with worldwide jurisdiction over continental confederations and, then, the only one that can confer a title on that level, ergo the title assigned by FIFA with Official Document to the winners of the Intercontinental Cup is legally a FIFA world title.\"  cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|last=|first=|date=|website=|page=19|format=PDF|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}} cfr.</ref><ref name=\"FIFA201732\">{{cite press release|date=27 October 2017|title=FIFA Council approves key organisational elements of the FIFA World Cup|url=https://www.fifa.com/about-fifa/news/y=2017/m=10/news=fifa-council-approves-key-organisational-elements-of-the-fifa-world-cu-2917722.html|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/fifa-acepta-propuesta-de-conembol-de-reconocer-titulos-de-copa-intercontinental-como-mundiales-de|title=FIFA acepta propuesta de CONMEBOL de reconocer t\u00edtulos de copa intercontinental como mundiales de clubes|date=29 October 2017|publisher=conmebol.com|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"kit201822\">{{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13|format=PDF}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Yamazaki-nabisco-Cup final 2004.jpg|thumb|left|300px|[[National Stadium (Tokyo)|Olympic Stadium]], [[Tokyo]], hosted the final]]\n{{-}}\n\n==Match details==\n{{footballbox\n|date       = 12 December 1982\n|time       =\n|team1      = [[Pe\u00f1arol]] {{flagicon|URU}}\n|score      = 2\u20130\n|report     = https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/61688/\n|team2  